comments.body:
> @dukenv0307 Thanks for the proposal. Your RCA is correct. However the solution does not seem to be the best to do here.

@s77rt I actually think the current way to do it is a workaround. Why would we need the datetime passed as param in order to know the timezone abbreviation? Only the selected timezone should be needed to get the abbreviation since it's a 1:1 map. 

We're working around it by constructing a date and extract the timezone from it, which is unnecessary and less performant IMO.
